<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">Written by someone who clearly knows absolutely nothing about trauma, trauma bonding or anything else related to systemic, horrific abuse. There&apos;s a r<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">Written by someone who clearly knows absolutely nothing about trauma, trauma bonding or anything else related to systemic, horrific abuse. There's a reason you don't understand. I'd focus on being grateful for that lack of understanding, instead of criticizing something that's outside your scope of comprehension. Let me guess? You also think it's super duper easy for victims of domestic violence to just get up and leave too, right? <a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
